    "title": {
        "rendered": "ToolbarGroup"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>A ToolbarGroup can be used to create subgroups of controls inside a <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/reference-guide/components/toolbar/toolbar/\">Toolbar</a>.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">import { Toolbar, ToolbarGroup, ToolbarButton } from '@wordpress/components';\nimport { paragraph, formatBold, formatItalic, link } from '@wordpress/icons';\n\nfunction MyToolbar() {\n    return (\n        &lt;Toolbar label=\"Options\"&gt;\n            &lt;ToolbarGroup&gt;\n                &lt;ToolbarButton icon={ paragraph } label=\"Paragraph\" /&gt;\n            &lt;/ToolbarGroup&gt;\n            &lt;ToolbarGroup&gt;\n                &lt;ToolbarButton icon={ formatBold } label=\"Bold\" /&gt;\n                &lt;ToolbarButton icon={ formatItalic } label=\"Italic\" /&gt;\n                &lt;ToolbarButton icon={ link } label=\"Link\" /&gt;\n            &lt;/ToolbarGroup&gt;\n        &lt;/Toolbar&gt;\n    );\n}\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Props</h3>\n<p>ToolbarGroup will pass all HTML props to the underlying element.</p>\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>ToolbarGroup may contain <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/reference-guide/components/toolbar/toolbar-button/\">ToolbarButton</a> and <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/reference-guide/components/toolbar/toolbar-item/\">ToolbarItem</a> as children.</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
